  "prompt": "When and how did Gautama Buddha die?",
  "response": "Gautama Buddha, the founder of Buddhism, is believed to have died around 483 BCE. According to traditional accounts, he passed away at the age of 80 in Kushinagar, present-day Uttar Pradesh, India. His death is often referred to as \"Parinirvana\" (or \"Mahaparinirvana\"), which signifies his passing into complete nirvana, having liberated himself from the cycle of birth, death, and rebirth.\n\nThe precise cause of his death is subject to various interpretations and accounts, but a common narrative suggests that he died after consuming a meal that may have contained spoiled food or something that caused illness. Despite the specific circumstances of his death, Buddhist teachings emphasize the impermanence of life and the attainment of nirvana as central themes of his passing.",
